OpenLayer 3 Designer - Example map: Synced map frames

This example map has been automaticly created by the OpenLayers 3 Designer. No code was written mannualy to produce this page, only button pushing was involved.

This map is synced to the one on the right - so moving one, moves the other.

The map shows countries of the world styled by colour. Data obtained from a world boundaries shapefile.

 

This map uses the same shapefile as the on on the right, however it shows the countries of the world styled by area.  Whilst this example uses the same files, synced maps can use any number of different layers, styles, popups and backgrounds

As many maps frames as you like can be synced to each other, there are no restrictions.
